The Federal Government has reiterated its determination to encourage meaningful agricultural activities that would further transform the lives of the people across the country. The Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Mu­hammed Mahmood Abubakar, gave the reassurance when he commissioned and handed over twoultra– modernsolarpowered boreholes in Umuduruoha and Obinuhu communities in the Nwangele and Nkwerre council areas of Imo state respectively. Represented by the Imo State Director of his minis­try, Pastor Chris Iwuchukwu O., the minister explained that the exercise was part of the demonstration and commitment of the Federal Government through his ministry to improve the lives of Nigerians resident in the rural areas. NYSC Gets Commendation On Innovative Service Delivery Absence of Governing Council Hindering AAU Progress, ASUU… The minister, who advised the benefiting communities to sustain their support to the Federal Government in its efforts to transform the nation for a better tomorrow, also enjoined them to guard against the vandalism of the projects and to always remain receptive to government’s policies and programmes to enable them to enjoy more democracy dividends.